from\": 1105, \"to\": 1123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These events encompass a spectrum of potential security concerns, including crowd surges, abandoned objects, and the presence or use of weapons, among others.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1284, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These events\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"a spectrum\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1159}, {\"ngram\": \"potential security concerns\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"crowd surges\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"abandoned objects\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1233}, {\"ngram\": \"the presence\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1251}, {\"ngram\": \"use\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"weapons\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1269}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1283}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore, specific thresholds can be manually configured to cater to individual event types, locations, or threats, enhancing the system's adaptability and efficacy.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1454, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"specific thresholds\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"individual event types\", \"from\": 1358, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"locations\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1391}, {\"ngram\": \"threats\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1403}, {\"ngram\": \"the system's adaptability\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1440}, {\"ngram\": \"efficacy\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"National and local law enforcement agencies, firefighters, and public transport security personnel will be equipped with access to AI-powered surveillance systems.\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"National and local law enforcement agencies\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1499}, {\"ngram\": \"firefighters\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1513}, {\"ngram\": \"public transport security personnel\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1554}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 1577, \"to\": 1583}, {\"ngram\": \"AI-powered surveillance systems\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1618}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Notably, Wintics' software, which underwent successful testing at the Depeche Mode concert, will be deployed across the Paris region and integrated into public transport networks.\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999713822949, \"rank\": 2.8617536436370843e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wintics' software\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1647}, {\"ngram\": \"successful testing\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"the Depeche Mode concert\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1711}, {\"ngram\": \"public transport networks\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Police Chief Laurent Nunez lauded the trial's outcome, expressing confidence in the system's readiness for widespread implementation.\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1802, \"end\": 1807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999713822949, \"rank\": 2.8617536436370843e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the trial's outcome\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1861}, {\"ngram\": \"confidence\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1884}, {\"ngram\": \"the system's readiness\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"widespread implementation\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 1940}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the technological advancements, French authorities have unequivocally stated that facial recognition will not be employed, citing concerns regarding privacy and civil liberties.\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19